<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="413" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,647]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,586,611]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2018" box="[349,495,586,611]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Cardiacephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angularis">
<emphasis box="[349,495,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">C. angularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinctive for its completely yellow body and swollen conical paracephalon (pointing dorsally) in combination with a smooth epicephalon and striate spermathecae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
